1970-01-01 00:20:00 Preheat your oven to 180 °C or gas mark 4

In a large mixing bowl, add the flour, baking powder and mixed spice. Mix together.

Add the butter, and rub these ingredients together by hand until they are breadcrumbs.

Add the dried fruit, sugar and milk and mix into a dough.

Spoon the dough into equal but rough portions on a greased baking tray

Sprinkle the Demerara sugar

Put into the oven for 20 minutes then air on a wire tray until cooled.

Enjoy!
